    • Method Detail

      • uiReadyISOMatchReport

        public static ExposureISOMatchReportBuilder uiReadyISOMatchReport()
        Creates a new, ui ready, ExposureISOMatchReportBuilder with the following fields set
        • Exposure - if an exposure is specified via onExposure or by using exposureBuilder.withISOMatchReport then use the specified exposure. Otherwise a new ui ready time vehicle damage exposure is created.
        • ClaimNumber - a unique claim number
        • DateOfLoss - set to a unique date before today
        • InsurerPhone - set to unique number of the form 123-123-123N
        • InsuringCompany - set to a unique title of the form InsuringCompanyN
        • MatchReasons - set to a unique reason of the form ReasonN
        • PolicyNumber - set to a unique number of the form 12-12345N
        • ReceivedDate - set to a unique date before today
          Returns:
          a new ui ready builder

        • withNonNullExposureISOSendDate

          public ExposureISOMatchReportBuilder withNonNullExposureISOSendDate()
          Ensures the ISOSendDate of the match report's exposure is a non null value. This is needed by the UI ready builder because if ISO claim level messaging is enabled the UI will not show the ISO tab on an exposure unless on of the exposures on the claim has a non null send date, indicating that this claim is doing exposure level ISO messaging. This method has no effect if the exposure's ISOSendDate is already set.
          Returns:
          the modified builder
